--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. ROOT-CAUSE / TOKENIZER FINDING (read from the artifact, not guessed)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Authoritative source = the .sp-tokenizer the daemon actually loads
(D:\F\shannon-prime-repos\models\gemma4-12b-b1.sp-tokenizer), parsed directly:
  SPTK header: ver 0.1, type_id=4 (GEMMA4_BPE), vocab=262144,
               bos=2  eos=106  pad=0  unk=3   (NB: header eos = 106 = <turn|>)
  SPTB blob:   nv=262144  n_merges=514906

  ids 0..4 : 0 <pad>  1 <eos>  2 <bos>  3 <unk>  4 <mask>
  REAL turn tokens (full-vocab scan for start_of/end_of/turn):
      105  '<|turn>'   = start-of-turn   (gemma's <start_of_turn> equivalent)
      106  '<turn|>'   = end-of-turn     (gemma's <end_of_turn> equivalent) = EOS
  There is NO '<start_of_turn>' and NO '<end_of_turn>' token anywhere in the vocab.
  multimodal soft tokens: 258882 '<image|>'  258883 '<audio|>'  (= generation_config suppress_tokens)
  role words are ordinary text tokens: 'user'=2364, 'model'=4368, '\n'=107.

BUG #1 (the operator's flag) — gemma3 template on a gemma4 model:
  gemma3_template() emitted the LITERAL strings "<start_of_turn>…<end_of_turn>".
  Those are not tokens here, and the gemma4 BPE blob lane has n_spec==0
  (src/tokenizer/gemma4_bpe.c:295 — sp_g4_encode special-splits NOTHING on the
  blob lane), so the literal strings shatter into ordinary text pieces
  (<, start, _of, _turn, >, …). The model was prompted in a format it was NEVER
  trained on -> rank-1 rode a suppressed soft token -> answer hung on a thin,
  FP-reorderable rank-2 margin (the coherent("Paris")<->garbage("cakes") flip).

BUG #2 (found while fixing #1) — the STOP token was being suppressed:
  <turn|>=106 is the end-of-turn / EOS token, but it matches the id-agnostic
  pipe-control suppress rule (<…|…>) -> it was masked to -inf in the sampler ->
  the model could NEVER emit it -> it answers correctly then runs on forever.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. FIX (gemma4-correct, config-driven, L2-only — no .cu / no sp_l1 / no submodule)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
tools/sp_daemon/src/tokenizer.rs:
  * apply_template_ids(): build the chat prompt directly at the TOKEN level using
    the REAL control ids (id-agnostic lookup): <bos> then per message
    <|turn>{role}\n{content}<turn|>\n , ending with the generation prompt
    <|turn>model\n . Only role label + content go through the proven C BPE
    encoder; the per-fragment forced BOS is stripped (encode_no_bos). Falls back
    to a minimal text template + <eos> if an artifact genuinely lacks turn tokens.
  * is_suppressed_control(): EXCLUDE <|turn>/<turn|> from suppression (they are
    the stop tokens, handled by turn_stop_ids/eos_ids — same treatment as <eos>).
  * eos_ids: add the real end-of-turn id <turn|> id-agnostically (decode stops by ID).
  * load_generation_config(): if generation_config.json sits beside the model,
    UNION its suppress_tokens + eos_token_id (the authoritative model contract);
    the id-agnostic rule stays the backstop (already covers 258882/258883).
tools/sp_daemon/src/routes.rs:
  * /v1/chat `messages` path now calls apply_template_ids (token-level prompt).
  * byteexact is now Option<bool>, DEFAULT ON for chat decode: the exact-integer
    islands + dual-prime CRT-NTT attention are run-to-run bit-identical AND
    build-independent (integer arithmetic) -> removes the FP-codegen reorder
    fragility. raw_logits:true or explicit byteexact:false opts out to the float path.

Verified prompt token ids ("What is the capital of France?"), from the daemon log:
  n=16  [2, 105, 2364, 107, 3689, 563, 506, 5279, 529, 7001, 236881, 106, 107, 105, 4368, 107]
  = <bos> <|turn> user \n <...content...> <turn|> \n <|turn> model \n   (CORRECT gemma-4 turn format)

lib unit tests: 57 passed; 0 failed (incl. updated suppress/turn classifiers).

